window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The days grow colder. The nights grow longer. And every time the moon rises, the wolf inside her grows a little stronger.</p> <p>Cheyenne Clark - a woman whose hatred for werewolves has turned her into the very beast she most despises - prowls the Arctic Circle on the trail of an ancient secret, hunting for the one thing that could remove the lycanthropic curse and make her human again.</p> <p>Yet standing between Chey and her goal are a werewolf hunter armed with a diabolically brilliant weapon, a centuries-old werewolf with her own mysterious agenda…and Chey’s own complicated feelings for the man who doomed her to this existence but on whom her life now depends.</p> <p>Worse, with every hour that passes, the wolf inside Chey becomes more powerful. It won’t be long before the woman disappears completely, and only the beast is left.</p>"; 
